        </p>
        <p>
            By the time I knew what I was doing the Internet couldn’t have been hotter. Business owners were
            scrambling for any kind of web presence. My friend and I saw the opportunity and started our own
            web design "firm". My friend did the graphics and I did the code and away we went. We even convinced
            our school to let us do several independent study classes to bolster our skills. When graduation
            came around I had made enough scratch to cover the first few years of college.
        </p>
        <h2>College years</h2>
        <p>
            Luckily, I was in college when the "bubble" burst. I was still making a few extra bucks on the side
            doing business-card web sites here and there. But I also did some pay-it-forward sites for friends
            and peers I’d hoped would make it big…
        </p>
        <p>
            Halfway through college I landed a paid internship at a local tech company. Not much web development
