            For several years I wore many hats - everything from business analyst to software engineer to data architect. I had
            the opportunity to build relationships with engineers, DBAs, product managers, sys admins, etc. and see
            how all of the moving pieces fit together. I was able to provide a lot of value on the application
            architecture and data engineering fronts. Data (relational and otherwise) just makes sense to me. I
            can extract it, transform it, and deliver it in a method that users understand - be it a CRUD app or BI
            reporting.
        </p>
        <h2>Corporate and beyond</h2>
        <p>
            I've logged a lot of time on ETL, reporting, and data architecture over the years. I've worked with systems
            running Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL, Tandem, Informix, Vertica, and others. Though lately I've spent most of
